		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;On Tuesday we met with Pete at Artisan&#39;s Asylum, where he showed us his &#39;DIY Loom&#39; project.  It&#39;s part of a 5-day &#39;Fiber to Fabric&#39; class that he is helping to create that will take students through the process of making textiles, from raw cotton to woven cloth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another class in this vein, which Pete has already helped create and run once, is &#39;Dirt to Machine&#39;, which involves melting down aluminum (eventually, they hope to start by smelting iron) and then building a small machine using metalworking tools in the machine shop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The current DIY loom design is a Dutch design that doesn&#39;t quite fit the planned class activities;  Pete is working on a re-design now.&lt;/p&gt;
